## 🏆 Complete Attack Chain

```
STAGE 1: Reconnaissance
  └─ LDAP enumeration reveals users, groups, services
  └─ Identify attack surface

STAGE 2: Targeting
  └─ Service account discovered (sqlservice with SPN)
  └─ Pre-auth disabled user discovered (vulnuser)

STAGE 3: Exploitation
  ├─ Kerberoasting: Extract sqlservice TGS ticket
  └─ ASREPRoasting: Extract vulnuser TGT ticket

STAGE 4: Cracking
  ├─ Hashcat: Crack TGS hash (TGS-REP)
  └─ Hashcat: Crack TGT hash (AS-REP)

STAGE 5: Compromise & Escalation
  ├─ sqlservice → Domain Admin
  ├─ vulnuser → Domain Admin
  └─ Complete domain control achieved

RESULT: 🎉 COMPLETE DOMAIN COMPROMISE
  ✅ Domain Admin privileges obtained
  ✅ Full network access achieved
  ✅ Lateral movement possible
  ✅ Persistence achievable
```

